Package core

Interface HlaPhysicalInterfaceManager

  • public interface HlaPhysicalInterfaceManager
    Manager used to manage HlaPhysicalInterfaces.

    This class is ThreadSafe as defined by Java Concurrency in Practice, see jcip.net.

      • addHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceListener

        void addHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaPhysicalInterfaceListener listener)
        Add a listener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaPhysicalInterface (Both local and remote). The listener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaPhysicalInterface is updated. The listener is also called when an interaction is sent to an instance of HlaPhysicalInterface. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add.

      • removeHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceListener

        void removeHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaPhysicalInterfaceListener listener)
        Remove a listener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaPhysicalInterface. Note: The listener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaPhysicalInterface. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to remove.

      • addHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void addHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaPhysicalInterfaceValueListener valueListener)
        Add a valueListener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaPhysicalInterface (Both local and remote). The Valuelistener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaPhysicalInterface is updated. Note that the attribute values that are notified are not guaranteed to be the latest available values for that attribute. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to add.

      • removeHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void removeHlaPhysicalInterfaceDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaPhysicalInterfaceValueListener valueListener)
        Remove a valueListener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaPhysicalInterface. Note: The valueListener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaPhysicalInterface. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to remove.

      • setEnabled

        void setEnabled​(boolean enabled)
        Enables or disables the HlaPhysicalInterface manager. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaPhysicalInterface manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable the HlaPhysicalInterface manager, otherwise false

      • setEnabledIfAvailableInFom

        void setEnabledIfAvailableInFom()
        Enables the HlaPhysicalInterface manager if it is available in the FOM at runtime. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaPhysicalInterface manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Check if the HlaPhysicalInterface manager is actually enabled when connected. An HlaPhysicalInterface manager may be disabled with the setEnabled(false) function, or it may be configured as if available in the FOM by the setEnabledIfAvailableInFom() function and then not available in the FOM at runtime.

        This method should only be used when connected, it will always return false when not connected.

        Returns:
        true if connected and the HlaPhysicalInterface manager is enabled.
